Release manager
Responsibilities 
·Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing a product release process that follows industry standards and best practices. The goal is to ensure that product releases are delivered on time and with high quality to ensure continued customer satisfaction. This will involve coordinating activities during the release planning stage, monitoring and controlling the release plan during the development and testing stage, and coordinating product launch.
·Responsible for ensuring there is a full suite of regression test procedures, test equipment, and test data for all functional and non-functional requirements. This will involve working closely with the organization (Development, Quality Assurance, Project Delivery, Customer Support, etc.) to ensure the regression test procedures are comprehensive, up-to-date, and effective. The regression test procedures must follow industry standards and best practices.
· Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing test automation to improve the efficiency of the release process while increasing test coverage and minimizing defect leakage. This will involve working closely with the Development team to prioritize functional areas that are good candidates for test automation, and managing the implementation of test automation tools and procedures.
· Responsible for supporting and following up AGILE delivery routines and procedures

Expected skills and qualifications:
·  Bachelor in Computer Science or related field.
·   Knowledge of industry standards for software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience in software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience implementing test automation is required.
·  Experience with Jira and Confluence is preferred.
·   Strong organizational skills are required.
·   Excellent communication (verbal and written) is required.
·   Ability to work independently to achieve operational goals.
·   Strong knowledgement of CDIC and devops automation
·   Knowledgement of code release strategy, branching and build cycles
·   Ability to understand the system dependencies and component dependencies and plan accordingly
·   Plus for SCRUM certification

Skills
Excellent communications skills
Candidate has to be fluent in English and Portuguese as this is a multi geography project with teams in Brazil/US/India

Release manager
Responsibilities 
·Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing a product release process that follows industry standards and best practices. The goal is to ensure that product releases are delivered on time and with high quality to ensure continued customer satisfaction. This will involve coordinating activities during the release planning stage, monitoring and controlling the release plan during the development and testing stage, and coordinating product launch.
·Responsible for ensuring there is a full suite of regression test procedures, test equipment, and test data for all functional and non-functional requirements. This will involve working closely with the organization (Development, Quality Assurance, Project Delivery, Customer Support, etc.) to ensure the regression test procedures are comprehensive, up-to-date, and effective. The regression test procedures must follow industry standards and best practices.
· Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing test automation to improve the efficiency of the release process while increasing test coverage and minimizing defect leakage. This will involve working closely with the Development team to prioritize functional areas that are good candidates for test automation, and managing the implementation of test automation tools and procedures.
· Responsible for supporting and following up AGILE delivery routines and procedures

Expected skills and qualifications:
·  Bachelor in Computer Science or related field.
·   Knowledge of industry standards for software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience in software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience implementing test automation is required.
·  Experience with Jira and Confluence is preferred.
·   Strong organizational skills are required.
·   Excellent communication (verbal and written) is required.
·   Ability to work independently to achieve operational goals.
·   Strong knowledgement of CDIC and devops automation
·   Knowledgement of code release strategy, branching and build cycles
·   Ability to understand the system dependencies and component dependencies and plan accordingly
·   Plus for SCRUM certification

Skills
Excellent communications skills
Candidate has to be fluent in English and Portuguese as this is a multi geography project with teams in Brazil/US/India

#jnVaga
Software Engineer - Mobile (APP) Pleno/Sênior
RESPONSABILIDADES E ATRIBUIÇÕES

Desenvolvimento do aplicativo para o Android e/ou IOS;
Refatorar e otimizar o código do projeto aplicando as melhores práticas;
Propor soluções alternativas para atender melhor as demandas de negócio;
Configuração de teste A/B e acompanhar o resultado dos experimentos para justificar as escolhas;
Propor soluções técnicas para os desafios de performance, de usabilidade e de novas tecnologias;
Manutenção de APIs
Atuar pro ativamente na detecção e na solução dos problemas nos times que têm relacionamento;

Ecossistemas que atua

Complexidade 1
Tarefa, item atômico e bem definido, onde o início, meio e fim estão claros. É inerente a entrega de itens desta complexidade que contemplem o fluxo adotado de revisão de código, contenham testes automatizados, respeitem estilo de código do projeto, tenham o mínimo de critério com relação a segurança e performance.

Complexidade 2
É um épico composto por várias tarefas, é geralmente uma refatoração, feature ou integração realizados dentro de um projeto existente. A entrega desta complexidade condiz em melhorar o projeto existente durante a feature/refatoração, documentação é adicionada, melhorias de performance são feitas, o design do código é evoluído e evidências desses exemplos são explicitadas na commit/pull request.

Complexidade 3
É a confecção de um projeto ou grande mudança que envolve outros sistemas ou mudanças sensíveis. Nesta complexidade a régua é o que temos de melhor na nossa stack no momento, se espera documentação exemplar de fluxos, detalhes de implementação, instruções para contribuição, cuidado e mecanismos para com performance, paths conhecidos-documentados-automatizados de disaster recovery, escalabilidade evidenciada em testes de performance, simplicidade e eficiência (que vão em direção oposta ao over-engineering).

REQUISITOS E QUALIFICAÇÕES
Conhecimentos e Experiência com:
Experiência em desenvolvimento de aplicações mobile Android e/ou IOS

Desejável conhecimentos em:
Testes automatizados;
Conhecimento de arquitetura de software.

Benefícios:

Plano de saúde e odontológico;
Vale-Refeição;
Vale-Alimentação;
Auxilio Educação;
Vale-Transporte;
Auxilio creche;
PLR;
Gympass;
Empréstimo Consignado;
Entre outros.
